td.p:
A ‘long-term resident’s EC residence permit’, in accordance with Article 2(g) of Council Directive 2003/109/EC of 25 November 2003 concerning the status of third-country nationals who are long-term residents (
OJ 2004 L 16, p. 44
), is a residence permit issued by the Member State concerned upon the acquisition of long-term resident status as provided for by that directive.
